memory, using examples from German-language, French, Italian, English, North American, Spanish-language and Hungarian literature. The essays seek to explore the theoretical roots of this interrelationship and to illustrate it through exemplary case presentations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCatastrophical, The, in literature. 0aCollective memory in literature. 0aMemory in literature. 4aErinnerungstheorie. 4aGedächtnis, kulturelles. 4aGedächtnisforschung. 4aSemiotik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  aMemory research.  asemiotics, cultural memory.1 aBannasch, Bettina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBirke, Dorothee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorsò, Vittoria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrodsky, Claudia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButter, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButzer, Günter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorbineau-Hoffmann, Angelika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHennigfeld, Ursula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHonold, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKalisky, Aurelia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlinkert, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlinkert, Thomas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKuon, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeuhofer, Monika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOesterle, Günter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.